   <div class="article_snippet_rdr">
    <h3>Flu or Cold Symptoms?</h3>
    <div class="snippet_fmt" id="art-snp">
     <p xmlns:xalan="http://xml.apache.org/xalan">When you wake up sneezing, coughing, and have that achy, feverish, can't move a muscle feeling, how do you know whether you have cold symptoms or the flu?</p>
     <p xmlns:xalan="http://xml.apache.org/xalan">It's important to know the difference between flu and cold symptoms. A cold is a milder respiratory illness than the flu. While cold symptoms can make you feel bad for a few days, flu symptoms can make you feel quite ill for a few days to weeks. The flu can also result in serious health problems such as pneumonia and hospitalizations.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="snippet_link">
     <a href="http://www.webmd.com/cold-and-flu/cold-guide/flu-cold-symptoms" onclick="return sl(this,'','art-snp_1');">Flu or Cold Symptoms?</a>
